The president is a super mortal and not just another ordinary Kenyan and therefore he cannot initiate any constitutional changes through a popular initiative. This is what defense lawyers in the ongoing BBi appeal case told the court as they urged judges to uphold the ruling of the high court. According to LSK president Nelson Havi who is leading the onslaught against appellants, BBI bill is unconstitutional as it interferes with the separation of powers between the 3 arms of government.
